# dotenvx encrypted env files
#
#   .env            — local dev (docker compose mounts this)
#   .env.production — production secrets (baked into Docker image)
#   .env.keys       — DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY (local only, never commit)
#
# Local docker compose (uses .env):
#   docker compose up --build
#
# Production server / DigitalOcean:
#   1. Edit production values:  dotenvx set KEY value -f .env.production
#   2. Commit .env.production (encrypted, safe)
#   3. Set DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY from .env.keys in platform secrets
#   4. Dockerfile copies .env.production → .env at build time; env.ts decrypts via DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY
#   5. DO workers: run_command is `node dist/worker.js` — DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY required on worker component
#   6. Transcripts: fetched directly from YouTube via youtube-transcript (works on residential IPs / local dev)
#
# Optional auth flags (dotenvx set KEY value -f .env):
#   EMAIL_PASSWORD_AUTH_ENABLED=true   # show email/password login (default: true)
#   EMAIL_PASSWORD_AUTH_ENABLED=false  # Google-only sign-in
#
# Ingestion & chat context tuning:
#   TRANSCRIPT_CANDIDATE_LIMIT=60      # videos scored per batch (default: 60)
#   PRESENCE_THRESHOLD=0.35            # creator-presence score cutoff (default: 0.35)
#   FALLBACK_SELECT_LIMIT=15             # fallback picks if none pass threshold
#   DEFAULT_SOURCE_VIDEO_LIMIT=150       # max videos listed from YouTube
#   CHUNK_TARGET_WORDS=300                # transcript chunk size at embed time
#   CREATOR_RAG_TOP_K=12                 # chunks retrieved per chat message
#   CREATOR_RAG_MIN_SCORE=0.72           # cosine score floor (falls back to top-k)
#   CHAT_MAX_CONTEXT_TOKENS=10000        # prompt token budget
#   TRANSCRIPT_FETCH_DELAY_MS=500        # delay between YouTube transcript fetches
#
# DigitalOcean Droplet (worker only, PM2):
#   1. git clone, npm ci, npm run build
#   2. export DOTENV_PRIVATE_KEY=...  (from .env.keys — add to ~/.bashrc on droplet)
#   3. npm run pm2:worker
#   4. pm2 startup && pm2 save   (auto-restart on reboot)
